inline_comments.message:
suggest to change to parentVertex;
add a space after the variable and before the colon. Also after the "for".
Please, use the ONAP Java coding style with column limit of 150 characteres: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Java+code+style.

Ok, I see. A little bit awkward but it works. The problem is that the present log in checkIfInUSe is done only for debugging purposes. In production, for example, debug logging level will be disabled, so it will be a wast to call that for logging purposes in all situations.
If you still want to do this for debug purposes, you should check here if the debug log is enabled and then call the filter, ex:

boolean isServiceInUse = false;
        if (log.isDebugEnabled()) {
            for (final GraphVertex graphVertex : allServiceVerticesToDelete) {
                if (checkIfInUse(graphVertex)) {
                    isServiceInUse = true;
                }
            }
//            isServiceInUse = allServiceVerticesToDelete.stream().filter(this::checkIfInUse).count() > 0;
        } else {
            isServiceInUse = allServiceVerticesToDelete.stream().anyMatch(this::checkIfInUse);
        }
        if (isServiceInUse) {
            throwStorageException(StorageOperationStatus.GRAPH_IS_LOCK);
        }

Still a little bit awkward to call the filter and after an any match for the same method, so for more clarity I would do a common for each. But it is just a suggestion.

And you could put this piece of code in a separate method, i.g boolean isAnyServiceInUse

You could do something like this:

for (GraphVertex currentParentVertex: parentVertices.left().value()) {
            GraphVertex currentVertex = currentParentVertex;
            while (currentVertex != null) {                
                Either<List<GraphVertex>, JanusGraphOperationStatus> currentVertexParentVertices =
                    janusGraphDao.getParentVertices(currentVertex, EdgeLabelEnum.VERSION, JsonParseFlagEnum.ParseAll);
                if (currentVertexParentVertices.isLeft()) {
                    allParents.addAll(currentVertexParentVertices.left().value());
                }
                allParents.add(currentVertex);
                currentVertex = janusGraphDao.getParentVertex(currentVertex, EdgeLabelEnum.VERSION, JsonParseFlagEnum.ParseAll)
                    .either(graphVertex -> graphVertex, janusGraphOperationStatus -> null);
            }
        }

if not, at least move the "parentVertex = janusGraphDao.getParentVertex(currentVertex, EdgeLabelEnum.VERSION, JsonParseFlagEnum.ParseAll);" to the last line of the while.

In general splitting up a long method like this into smaller well names methods improves code readability and therefore maintainability. 
I would suggest extracting this bit out to a method called getVerticesForAllVersions(), so this code here would be reduced to:
List<GraphVertex> allServiceVerticesToDelete = getVerticesForAllVersions(invariantUUID);
